Project IceStorm – iCE40 HX1K RAMT Tile (3 16)

Project IceStorm aims at documenting the bitstream format of Lattice iCE40 FPGAs and providing simple tools for analyzing and creating bitstream files. This is work in progress.

This page describes the RAMT Tile (3 16), what nets and configuration bits it has and how it is connected to its neighbourhood.

Configuration Bitmap

A RAMT Tile has 672 config bits in 16 groups of 42 bits each:
 B0[41:0],  B1[41:0],  B2[41:0],  B3[41:0],  B4[41:0],  B5[41:0],  B6[41:0],  B7[41:0],
 B8[41:0],  B9[41:0], B10[41:0], B11[41:0], B12[41:0], B13[41:0], B14[41:0], B15[41:0]
